Package: psplinePsd
Type: Package
Title: Spectral density estimation using P-spline priors
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Patricio Maturana-Russel [aut, cre],
        Renate Meyer [aut]
Maintainer: Patricio Maturana-Russel <p.russel@auckland.ac.nz>
Description: Implementation of a Metropolis-within-Gibbs MCMC algorithm to estimate the spectral density of a stationary time series using P-spline priors.  The algorithm makes use of the Whittle likelihood to produce pseudo-posterior samples and is based on the work presented in Maturana-Russel, P. and Meyer, R. arXiv:1905.01832.  This package follows the bsplinePsd package structure.
License: GPL (>= 3)
Imports: Rcpp, expm, fields, fda
LinkingTo: Rcpp
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 7.0.2
NeedsCompilation: yes
